President Biden delivered a speech at Central New Mexico Community College in Albuquerque, where he discussed his plan for student debt relief. He emphasized the importance of providing relief to working- and middle-class Americans who are still recovering from the economic crisis caused by the pandemic. The plan includes up to $10,000 in student debt relief, and up to $20,000 for those who received a Pell Grant. The application process is simple and can be completed online. President Biden also highlighted other measures his administration is taking to make education more affordable, such as fixing the Public Service Loan Forgiveness program and making changes to income-driven repayment plans. He addressed criticism from Republican officials and emphasized that the relief plan is focused on helping working people and the middle class. The speech concluded with President Biden expressing optimism about the future and the potential of the United States.